{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, to effectively use LLMs for coding, you still need to understand",
    "enough about the programming language to understand whether the outputs are correct or not.",
    "In addition to generating code, LLMs can also help with the following routine coding activities (see also Lubiana et al., 2023).",
    "It is not uncommon to have code that you did not write (e.g., taken from a paper, a collaborator, GitHub, or StackOverflow) or code that you wrote in the past and did not document well.",
    "With good prompts, LLMs can explain what the code is doing and why."
  ]
}